How to Install Chrome on Ubuntu Using GUI


Step 1: Open Any Browser and Download .deb package (for Debian/Ubuntu)

Search for Google Chrome on your available browser or directly click on this Google Chrome downloading link.
https://www.google.com/chrome/?platform=linux

Step 2: Choose Your Options > Click on Accept and Install
Select the first option 64-bit.deb (for Debian/Ubuntu).
After that Click on the “Accept and Install” Button.


Step 3: Open Terminal 
cd Downloads/
sudo dpkg -i <downloaded-filename.deb>

